def evaluate_linear_expr( expression: Union[LinearExpr, IntVar, int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64], solution: ortools.sat.cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse) -> int: 
3065def evaluate_linear_expr(
3066    expression: LinearExprT, solution: cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse
3067) -> int:
3068    """Evaluate a linear expression against a solution."""
3069    if isinstance(expression, IntegralTypes):
3070        return int(expression)
3071    if not isinstance(expression, LinearExpr):
3072        raise TypeError("Cannot interpret %s as a linear expression." % expression)
3073
3074    value = 0
3075    to_process = [(expression, 1)]
3076    while to_process:
3077        expr, coeff = to_process.pop()
3078        if isinstance(expr, IntegralTypes):
3079            value += int(expr) * coeff
3080        elif isinstance(expr, _ProductCst):
3081            to_process.append((expr.expression(), coeff * expr.coefficient()))
3082        elif isinstance(expr, _Sum):
3083            to_process.append((expr.left(), coeff))
3084            to_process.append((expr.right(), coeff))
3085        elif isinstance(expr, _SumArray):
3086            for e in expr.expressions():
3087                to_process.append((e, coeff))
3088            value += expr.constant() * coeff
3089        elif isinstance(expr, _WeightedSum):
3090            for e, c in zip(expr.expressions(), expr.coefficients()):
3091                to_process.append((e, coeff * c))
3092            value += expr.constant() * coeff
3093        elif isinstance(expr, IntVar):
3094            value += coeff * solution.solution[expr.index]
3095        elif isinstance(expr, _NotBooleanVariable):
3096            value += coeff * (1 - solution.solution[expr.negated().index])
3097        else:
3098            raise TypeError(f"Cannot interpret {expr} as a linear expression.")
3099
3100    return value

Evaluate a linear expression against a solution.

def evaluate_boolean_expression( literal: Union[IntVar, ortools.sat.python.cp_model._NotBooleanVariable, int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64, bool], solution: ortools.sat.cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse) -> bool: 
3103def evaluate_boolean_expression(
3104    literal: LiteralT, solution: cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse
3105) -> bool:
3106    """Evaluate a boolean expression against a solution."""
3107    if isinstance(literal, IntegralTypes):
3108        return bool(literal)
3109    elif isinstance(literal, IntVar) or isinstance(literal, _NotBooleanVariable):
3110        index: int = cast(Union[IntVar, _NotBooleanVariable], literal).index
3111        if index >= 0:
3112            return bool(solution.solution[index])
3113        else:
3114            return not solution.solution[-index - 1]
3115    else:
3116        raise TypeError(f"Cannot interpret {literal} as a boolean expression.")

Evaluate a boolean expression against a solution.

class CpSolver: 
3119class CpSolver:
3120    """Main solver class.
3121
3122    The purpose of this class is to search for a solution to the model provided
3123    to the solve() method.
3124
3125    Once solve() is called, this class allows inspecting the solution found
3126    with the value() and boolean_value() methods, as well as general statistics
3127    about the solve procedure.
3128    """
3129
3130    def __init__(self) -> None:
3131        self.__solution: Optional[cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse] = None
3132        self.parameters: sat_parameters_pb2.SatParameters = (
3133            sat_parameters_pb2.SatParameters()
3134        )
3135        self.log_callback: Optional[Callable[[str], None]] = None
3136        self.best_bound_callback: Optional[Callable[[float], None]] = None
3137        self.__solve_wrapper: Optional[swig_helper.SolveWrapper] = None
3138        self.__lock: threading.Lock = threading.Lock()
3139
3140    def solve(
3141        self,
3142        model: CpModel,
3143        solution_callback: Optional["CpSolverSolutionCallback"] = None,
3144    ) -> cp_model_pb2.CpSolverStatus:
3145        """Solves a problem and passes each solution to the callback if not null."""
3146        with self.__lock:
3147            self.__solve_wrapper = swig_helper.SolveWrapper()
3148
3149        self.__solve_wrapper.set_parameters(self.parameters)
3150        if solution_callback is not None:
3151            self.__solve_wrapper.add_solution_callback(solution_callback)
3152
3153        if self.log_callback is not None:
3154            self.__solve_wrapper.add_log_callback(self.log_callback)
3155
3156        if self.best_bound_callback is not None:
3157            self.__solve_wrapper.add_best_bound_callback(self.best_bound_callback)
3158
3159        solution: cp_model_pb2.CpSolverResponse = self.__solve_wrapper.solve(
3160            model.proto
3161        )
3162        self.__solution = solution
3163
3164        if solution_callback is not None:
3165            self.__solve_wrapper.clear_solution_callback(solution_callback)
3166
3167        with self.__lock:
3168            self.__solve_wrapper = None
3169
3170        return solution.status
3171
3172    def stop_search(self) -> None:
3173        """Stops the current search asynchronously."""
3174        with self.__lock:
3175            if self.__solve_wrapper:
3176                self.__solve_wrapper.stop_search()
3177
3178    def value(self, expression: LinearExprT) -> int:
3179        """Returns the value of a linear expression after solve."""
3180        return evaluate_linear_expr(expression, self._solution)

3186        variables. If `variables` is a `pd.Series` indexed by the underlying

3194        Returns:

3197        solution = self._solution

3199            func=lambda v: solution.solution[v.index],
3200            values=variables,

Main solver class.

The purpose of this class is to search for a solution to the model provided to the solve() method.

Once solve() is called, this class allows inspecting the solution found with the value() and boolean_value() methods, as well as general statistics about the solve procedure.

class CpSolverSolutionCallback(ortools.sat.python.swig_helper.SolutionCallback): 
3418class CpSolverSolutionCallback(swig_helper.SolutionCallback):
3419    """Solution callback.
3420
3421    This class implements a callback that will be called at each new solution
3422    found during search.
3423
3424    The method on_solution_callback() will be called by the solver, and must be
3425    implemented. The current solution can be queried using the boolean_value()
3426    and value() methods.
3427
3428    These methods returns the same information as their counterpart in the
3429    `CpSolver` class.
3430    """
3431
3432    def __init__(self) -> None:
3433        swig_helper.SolutionCallback.__init__(self)
3434
3435    def OnSolutionCallback(self) -> None:
3436        """Proxy for the same method in snake case."""
3437        self.on_solution_callback()
3438
3439    def boolean_value(self, lit: LiteralT) -> bool:
3440        """Returns the boolean value of a boolean literal.
3441
3442        Args:
3443            lit: A boolean variable or its negation.
3444
3445        Returns:
3446            The Boolean value of the literal in the solution.
3447
3448        Raises:
3449            RuntimeError: if `lit` is not a boolean variable or its negation.
3450        """
3451        if not self.has_response():
3452            raise RuntimeError("solve() has not been called.")
3453        if isinstance(lit, IntegralTypes):
3454            return bool(lit)
3455        if isinstance(lit, IntVar) or isinstance(lit, _NotBooleanVariable):
3456            return self.SolutionBooleanValue(
3457                cast(Union[IntVar, _NotBooleanVariable], lit).index
3458            )
3459        if cmh.is_boolean(lit):
3460            return bool(lit)
3461        raise TypeError(f"Cannot interpret {lit} as a boolean expression.")
3462
3463    def value(self, expression: LinearExprT) -> int:
3464        """Evaluates an linear expression in the current solution.
3465
3466        Args:
3467            expression: a linear expression of the model.
3468
3469        Returns:
3470            An integer value equal to the evaluation of the linear expression
3471            against the current solution.
3472
3473        Raises:
3474            RuntimeError: if 'expression' is not a LinearExpr.
3475        """
3476        if not self.has_response():
3477            raise RuntimeError("solve() has not been called.")
3478
3479        value = 0
3480        to_process = [(expression, 1)]
3481        while to_process:
3482            expr, coeff = to_process.pop()
3483            if isinstance(expr, IntegralTypes):
3484                value += int(expr) * coeff
3485            elif isinstance(expr, _ProductCst):
3486                to_process.append((expr.expression(), coeff * expr.coefficient()))
3487            elif isinstance(expr, _Sum):
3488                to_process.append((expr.left(), coeff))
3489                to_process.append((expr.right(), coeff))
3490            elif isinstance(expr, _SumArray):
3491                for e in expr.expressions():
3492                    to_process.append((e, coeff))
3493                    value += expr.constant() * coeff
3494            elif isinstance(expr, _WeightedSum):
3495                for e, c in zip(expr.expressions(), expr.coefficients()):
3496                    to_process.append((e, coeff * c))
3497                value += expr.constant() * coeff
3498            elif isinstance(expr, IntVar):
3499                value += coeff * self.SolutionIntegerValue(expr.index)
3500            elif isinstance(expr, _NotBooleanVariable):
3501                value += coeff * (1 - self.SolutionIntegerValue(expr.negated().index))
3502            else:
3503                raise TypeError(
3504                    f"cannot interpret {expression} as a linear expression."
3505                )
3506
3507        return value
3508
3509    def has_response(self) -> bool:
3510        return self.HasResponse()
3511
3512    def stop_search(self) -> None:
3513        """Stops the current search asynchronously."""
3514        if not self.has_response():
3515            raise RuntimeError("solve() has not been called.")
3516        self.StopSearch()
3517

3523        return self.ObjectiveValue()

Solution callback.

This class implements a callback that will be called at each new solution found during search.

The method on_solution_callback() will be called by the solver, and must be implemented. The current solution can be queried using the boolean_value() and value() methods.

These methods returns the same information as their counterpart in the CpSolver class.

def boolean_value( self, lit: Union[IntVar, ortools.sat.python.cp_model._NotBooleanVariable, int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64, bool]) -> bool: 
3439    def boolean_value(self, lit: LiteralT) -> bool:
3440        """Returns the boolean value of a boolean literal.
3441
3442        Args:
3443            lit: A boolean variable or its negation.
3444
3445        Returns:
3446            The Boolean value of the literal in the solution.
3447
3448        Raises:
3449            RuntimeError: if `lit` is not a boolean variable or its negation.
3450        """
3451        if not self.has_response():
3452            raise RuntimeError("solve() has not been called.")
3453        if isinstance(lit, IntegralTypes):
3454            return bool(lit)
3455        if isinstance(lit, IntVar) or isinstance(lit, _NotBooleanVariable):
3456            return self.SolutionBooleanValue(
3457                cast(Union[IntVar, _NotBooleanVariable], lit).index
3458            )
3459        if cmh.is_boolean(lit):
3460            return bool(lit)
3461        raise TypeError(f"Cannot interpret {lit} as a boolean expression.")

Returns the boolean value of a boolean literal.

Arguments:
  • lit: A boolean variable or its negation.
Returns:

The Boolean value of the literal in the solution.

Raises:
  • RuntimeError: if lit is not a boolean variable or its negation.
def value( self, expression: Union[LinearExpr, IntVar, int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64]) -> int: 
3463    def value(self, expression: LinearExprT) -> int:
3464        """Evaluates an linear expression in the current solution.
3465
3466        Args:
3467            expression: a linear expression of the model.
3468
3469        Returns:
3470            An integer value equal to the evaluation of the linear expression
3471            against the current solution.
3472
3473        Raises:
3474            RuntimeError: if 'expression' is not a LinearExpr.
3475        """
3476        if not self.has_response():
3477            raise RuntimeError("solve() has not been called.")
3478
3479        value = 0
3480        to_process = [(expression, 1)]
3481        while to_process:
3482            expr, coeff = to_process.pop()
3483            if isinstance(expr, IntegralTypes):
3484                value += int(expr) * coeff
3485            elif isinstance(expr, _ProductCst):
3486                to_process.append((expr.expression(), coeff * expr.coefficient()))
3487            elif isinstance(expr, _Sum):
3488                to_process.append((expr.left(), coeff))
3489                to_process.append((expr.right(), coeff))
3490            elif isinstance(expr, _SumArray):
3491                for e in expr.expressions():
3492                    to_process.append((e, coeff))
3493                    value += expr.constant() * coeff
3494            elif isinstance(expr, _WeightedSum):
3495                for e, c in zip(expr.expressions(), expr.coefficients()):
3496                    to_process.append((e, coeff * c))
3497                value += expr.constant() * coeff
3498            elif isinstance(expr, IntVar):
3499                value += coeff * self.SolutionIntegerValue(expr.index)
3500            elif isinstance(expr, _NotBooleanVariable):
3501                value += coeff * (1 - self.SolutionIntegerValue(expr.negated().index))
3502            else:
3503                raise TypeError(
3504                    f"cannot interpret {expression} as a linear expression."
3505                )
3506
3507        return value

Evaluates an linear expression in the current solution.

Arguments:
  • expression: a linear expression of the model.
Returns:

An integer value equal to the evaluation of the linear expression against the current solution.

Raises:
  • RuntimeError: if 'expression' is not a LinearExpr.

3610    def on_solution_callback(self) -> None:
3611        """Called on each new solution."""
3612        current_time = time.time()
3613        obj = self.objective_value
3614        print(
3615            "Solution %i, time = %0.2f s, objective = %i"

3617        )

class VarArrayAndObjectiveSolutionPrinter(CpSolverSolutionCallback): 
3625class VarArrayAndObjectiveSolutionPrinter(CpSolverSolutionCallback):
3626    """Print intermediate solutions (objective, variable values, time)."""
3627
3628    def __init__(self, variables: Sequence[IntVar]) -> None:
3629        CpSolverSolutionCallback.__init__(self)
3630        self.__variables: Sequence[IntVar] = variables
3631        self.__solution_count: int = 0
3632        self.__start_time: float = time.time()
3633
3634    def on_solution_callback(self) -> None:
3635        """Called on each new solution."""
3636        current_time = time.time()
3637        obj = self.objective_value
3638        print(
3639            "Solution %i, time = %0.2f s, objective = %i"
3640            % (self.__solution_count, current_time - self.__start_time, obj)
3641        )
3642        for v in self.__variables:
3643            print("  %s = %i" % (v, self.value(v)), end=" ")
3644        print()
3645        self.__solution_count += 1
3646

3648    def solution_count(self) -> int:
3649        """Returns the number of solutions found."""
3650        return self.__solution_count
